- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper proposes a modification to a template-based invariant synthesis algorithm. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is likely because the paper deals with algebraic invariants and polynomial templates. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is likely because the paper discusses the use of invariants in the context of imperative programs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with program verification and correctness.
